3880   // null and free calls, delete the calls and replace the comparisons with true
3881   // or false as appropriate.
3882 
3883   // This is based on the principle that we can substitute our own allocation
3884   // function (which will never return null) rather than knowledge of the
3885   // specific function being called. In some sense this can change the permitted
3886   // outputs of a program (when we convert a malloc to an alloca, the fact that
3887   // the allocation is now on the stack is potentially visible, for example),
3888   // but we believe in a permissible manner.
3889   SmallVector<WeakTrackingVH, 64> Users;
